ZH: 这只流浪猫被遗弃在街上。
EN: The stray cat was abandoned on the street.

ZH: 他曾经被遗弃在孤儿院。
EN: He was once abandoned at an orphanage.

ZH: 遗弃儿童常常面临生存的困境。
EN: Abandoned children often face difficulties in survival.

ZH: 这座建筑物已经遭到遗弃多年。
EN: This building has been abandoned for many years.

ZH: 好友的背叛让他感到被遗弃了。
EN: The betrayal of a friend made him feel abandoned.

ZH: 许多人不愿意遗弃旧习惯。
EN: Many people are reluctant to abandon old habits.

ZH: 她发誓绝不遗弃她的爱人。
EN: She swore to never abandon her loved one.

ZH: 这个城市的废弃工厂遭到了遗弃。
EN: The abandoned factory in this city has been neglected.

ZH: 我们不能遗弃我们的责任。
EN: We cannot abandon our responsibilities.

ZH: 他们决定遗弃这个项目并开始新的计划。
EN: They decided to abandon this project and start a new plan.

ZH: 遗弃婴儿是不道德的行为。
EN: Abandoning a baby is an unethical act.

ZH: 这个国家的孤儿很容易被遗弃。
EN: Orphans in this country are easily abandoned.

ZH: 遗弃信仰会让人感到内心空虚。
EN: Abandoning one's beliefs can leave a person feeling empty inside.

ZH: 他愿意遗弃一切去追求自己的梦想。
EN: He is willing to abandon everything to pursue his dreams.

ZH: 那只小狗非常幸运，因为它没有被遗弃。
EN: The little dog is very lucky because it was not abandoned.

ZH: 她从小就被遗弃，没有父母的关爱。
EN: She was abandoned since childhood, without the care of parents.

ZH: 这个废弃的房子充满了遗弃和荒凉的气息。
EN: This abandoned house is filled with a sense of abandonment and desolation.

ZH: 他的母亲遗弃了他，从未给予过关心。
EN: His mother abandoned him and never showed any care.

ZH: 那个地方给人一种被遗弃的感觉。
EN: That place gives a feeling of being abandoned.

ZH: 遗弃动物是一种残忍的行为。
EN: Abandoning animals is a cruel act.

ZH: 他感到无助和遗弃之感。
EN: He felt helpless and abandoned.
